[In the US, almost all of the people who are dying from COVID-19 now are unvaccinated.

The Associated Press reports that the number of deaths per day has declined to fewer than 300 a day. Data analyzed from May 2021 reveals that "breakthrough" infections -- people who are fully vaccinated and have the virus -- make up less than 1200 of the current 853 000 COVID hospitalizations, or 0.1 percent of hospitalizations.

CDC Director Dr. Rochelle Walensky said this week that the vaccines are "nearly 100% effective against severe disease and death," adding that "nearly every death, especially among adults, due to COVID-19, is, at this point, entirely preventable." (from https://www.complex.com/life/almost-all-americans-now-dying-from-covid-unvaccinated).

It is these unvaccinated individuals who are particularly at high risk for the delta variant. How to convince the vaccine holdouts of the value of the vaccine is a dilemma. - Mod.LK]

