[In the past 24 hours, 9 countries including Brazil (64 134), India (49 851), Colombia (33 594), Russia (21 665), Indonesia (21 095), Argentina (18 555), UK (18 185), South Africa (17 956), and the USA (15 537) have reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 8108 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 24 Jun 2021 to late 25 Jun 2021). A total of 43 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 17 of the 43 countries are from the European region, 7 are from the Americas region, 6 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the Southeast Asia region, 4 are from the Western Pacific region, and 4 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 0.96%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 12.3%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 3.0% increase in daily reported cases and a 6.2% increase in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily total: over 350 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours, with over 181.54 million cumulative reported cases and over 3.93 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
